 《连线》对 HyperSport 进行了测试。 （ <a href="https://www.wired.com/story/first-ride-damon-motors-hypersport/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">有线</a>）</p><p> •<strong>消费者的支出与 2019 年一样</strong>：随着支出的增加以及客户更看重体验而非商品，疫情引发的消费狂潮逐渐消退。 ( <a href="https://www.wsj.com/business/retail/consumers-are-spending-like-its-2019-dff7b8bc" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Wall Street Journal</a> )</p><p> •<strong>皮肤塑造健康的奇怪方式</strong>：风化或不健康的皮肤正在成为几乎所有与年龄相关的疾病（从帕金森病到2 型糖尿病）的主要危险因素。 （ <a href="https://www.bbc.com/future/article/20230823-the-curious-ways-your-skin-shapes-your-health" target="_blank" rel="noopener">英国广播公司</a>）</p><p> •<strong>报告发现，封锁和口罩“明确”地减少了新冠病毒的传播</strong>：皇家学会的审查着眼于多种措施组合应用时的非药物干预措施。 （ <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/24/lockdowns-face-masks-unequivocally-cut-spread-covid-study-finds" target="_blank" rel="noopener">《卫报</a>》）</p><p> •<strong>是什么让Vivek 如此烦人？一项调查</strong>。盖伊竞选总统组 哈佛大学毕业生维韦克·拉马斯瓦米 (Vivek Ramaswamy) 对于任何去过那里的人来说都是一个很难辨认的人物，即使我们从来不认识他本人。 （<a href="https://www.joshbarro.com/p/section-guy-runs-for-president" target="_blank" rel="noopener">非常严肃</a>）</p><p> •<strong>一场胜利，17,000 场失败——华盛顿将军的生活</strong>。与环球旅行者队所受到的普遍赞美相反，那些穿着将军队臭名昭著的不成功绿色球衣的人在失败期间、失败后、失败后遭到嘘声、嘲笑和扣篮。 （<a href="https://www.bbc.com/sport/basketball/66525597" target="_blank" rel="noopener">英国广播公司</a>）</p></blockquote><p> Be sure to check out our <a href="https://ritholtz.com/category/podcast/mib/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-web-url="http://www.bloombergview.com/topics/masters-in-business">Masters in Business</a> <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/masters-in-business/id730188152?mt=2" data-web-url="https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/masters-in-business/id730188152?mt=2">interview</a> this weekend with Greg Davis, Chief Investment Officer of the Vanguard Group. Davis is responsible for the oversight of approximately $7 trillion managed by Vanguard fixed income, equity index, and quantitative equity groups. He also serves as a member of the Treasury Borrowing Advisory Committee of the US Treasury Department.</p><p></p><p><strong>如果 10 年期国债利率上升（64% 的情况下），同期股市平均下跌 0.15%。如果 10 年期利率在 30 天内下降，标准普尔 500 指数同期上涨 3.1%</strong><br /> <a href="https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/stocksandrates.jpeg" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone wp-image-318768" src="https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/stocksandrates.jpeg" alt="" width="700" height="438" srcset="https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/stocksandrates.jpeg 872w, https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/stocksandrates-300x188.jpeg 300w, https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/stocksandrates-768x481.jpeg 768w, https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/stocksandrates-250x157.jpeg 250w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></a><br />资料来源： <a href="https://theirrelevantinvestor.com/2023/08/22/rates-rule-everything-around-me/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">无关投资者</a></p><p></p><p><a class="gtrackexternal" href="https://mailchi.mp/005fb77d75b9/ritholtzreads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>Sign up for our reads-only mailing list here</em></a> .</p><p></p><p><a rel="nofollow" href="https://ritholtz.com/2023/08/10-monday-am-reads-400/">周一上午 10 点阅读的</a>帖子首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://ritholtz.com">The Big Picture</a>上。</p> ;
